name: $resourceType
desc: Returns the FHIR type name for this instance

name: $::name
desc: Returns: A natural language name identifying the naming system. This name should be usable as an identifier for the module by machine processing applications such as code generation.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: A natural language name identifying the naming system. This name should be usable as an identifier for the module by machine processing applications such as code generation.

name: $status
desc: Returns: The status of this naming system. Enables tracking the life-cycle of the content.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The status of this naming system. Enables tracking the life-cycle of the content.

name: $kind
desc: Returns: Indicates the purpose for the naming system - what kinds of things does it make unique?

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Indicates the purpose for the naming system - what kinds of things does it make unique?

name: $date
desc: Returns: The date  (and optionally time) when the naming system was published. The date must change when the business version changes and it must change if the status code changes. In addition, it should change when the substantive content of the naming system changes.

pvardefs.name: pValue

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The name of the organization or individual that published the naming system.

name: $contact
desc: Returns: Contact details to assist a user in finding and communicating with the publisher.

name: $::type
desc: Returns: Categorizes a naming system for easier search by grouping related naming systems.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Categorizes a naming system for easier search by grouping related naming systems.

name: $description
desc: Returns: A free text natural language description of the naming system from a consumer's perspective. Details about what the namespace identifies including scope, granularity, version labeling, etc.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: A free text natural language description of the naming system from a consumer's perspective. Details about what the namespace identifies including scope, granularity, version labeling, etc.

name: $useContext
desc: Returns: The content was developed with a focus and intent of supporting the contexts that are listed. These contexts may be general categories (gender, age, ...) or may be references to specific programs (insurance plans, studies, ...) and may be used to assist with indexing and searching for appropriate naming system instances.
